BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Poetry Month: Meet the Author - Gianna Patriarca
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260418T153000
UID:69b57d6b67801235ed71fa55@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:April is National Poetry Month.  Join us for a celebration of 
 literature as author\, Gianna Patriarca\, reads from her thirteenth book: 
 “Ciociara/?/Canadese”\, and selections of her literary work\, includin
 g poetry\, short fiction and children’s literature.  Performed in spoken
  word\, narrative\, and monologue.\nGianna is an award winning author of 1
 3 books\, including poetry and short fiction.  Gianna holds a Bachelor of 
 Arts in English Literature with a Minor in Italian Studies and a Bachelor 
 of Education\, both from York University\n.
LOCATION:Humber Summit\, Auditorium\, Lower level.
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b57d6b67801235ed71fa55
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
