UID:6970f87276261f280065b596@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This program introduces children to beginner computer programm
 ing and fosters the development of essential STEM skills. Delivered in col
 laboration with Macaulay Centres for Children\, the initiative focuses on 
 promoting educational growth and enhancing future employment opportunities
 \, particularly for children in marginalized communities. Participants wil
 l engage in hands-on coding activities\, make new friends\, and have fun i
 n a supportive. Space is limited\, and advance registration with a commitm
 ent to attend the full session is required.
LOCATION:Woodview Park\, Program Room
