UID:69b30a74b48451fc3c087655@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Learn to make a 2D Platformer using this free browser-based vi
 deo game development tool.\nLearn the basics of video game development usi
 ng Construct 3\, a free browser-based game engine. In this follow-up to th
 e Intro to Construct 3 class\, participants will learn how to import art a
 nd create animations\, and add different types of platforms types.\nThis i
 s an in-person program. Registration is required.\nRegistration begins on 
 April 16th at 12:30pm. Note: Your spot will not be guaranteed after 5 minu
 tes of the start of the program.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe pers
 onal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Library u
 nder the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The in
 formation will only be used for event and program registration\, delivery 
 and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your information c
 an be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\
 , 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8
LOCATION:North York Central Library\, 2nd Floor - eLearning Lab
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b30a74b48451fc3c087655
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
