BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Investing 101: What You Need to Know
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T200000
UID:69b2f65db48451fc3c086dbe@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Whether you are starting out or learning more about your curre
 nt investments\, this seminar will help you make sense of the complex worl
 d of investing. We will cover the three asset classes: stocks\, bonds\, an
 d cash plus simple ways to get started with investing. In this easy-to-und
 erstand seminar\, Teri will set out the advantages of each of the three ma
 jor tax-sheltered investing plans for Canadians: Tax-Free Savings Accounts
  (TFSAs)\, Registered Retirement Savings Plans (RRSPs) and the new First H
 ome Savings Accounts (FHSAs).\nPresented by Teri Courchene\, BA\, MA\, M
 Ed\, CSC. Teri is a former investing instructor at U of T School of Conti
 nuing Studies and former director of economic research at a major bank. On
 e of her current volunteer roles is giving investing and finance talks at 
 Toronto Public Library branches.\nPlease note that space is limited.
LOCATION:Pape/Danforth\, 2nd floor program room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b2f65db48451fc3c086dbe
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
