UID:69b07b181e64afd01e61361a@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to use this amazing and powerful tool that is used f
 or video recording and live streaming. OBS Studio is free and open source.
 \nFor anyone who wants to record videos for YouTube or stream their conten
 t live\, OBS Studio is an amazing tool that can achieve this very easily.\
 nThe program is very user-friendly with easy to use tools that can create 
 an unlimited number of scenes that you can switch between seamlessly via c
 ustom transitions.\nIn the class will create a multi-scene setup all while
  using different configurations that include the following:\nDisplay Captu
 re\nAudio Input Capture\nVideo Capture Device\nLogo\nText\nand more.\nRegi
 stration is required for this class. You can order free tickets by clickin
 g the link below. Tickets will become available one week prior to the clas
 s at 9 a.m.\nInformation Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on t
 his form is collected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libra
 ries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only b
 e used for event and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Quest
 ions about how the library handles your information can be directed to Ans
 werline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, 
 Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Agincourt\, Learning Centre
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b07b181e64afd01e61361a
