BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Writers are Superstars!
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260401T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260401T173000
UID:69b1b8f46583d22e3c0ea9e8@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Come join us for a fun interactive workshop with Author Kern C
 arter.\nWriters Are Superstars is a hands-on workshop that shows how writi
 ng is behind almost everything we enjoy—TV shows\, video games\, books\,
  social media\, and more. Through quick activities and creative challenges
 \, students will get to try different types of writing and see what fits t
 heir style. By the end\, they’ll walk away with a better sense of how wr
 iting can be fun\, expressive\, and even something you can build a career 
 around.\nDrop In. No Registration Required.
LOCATION:Amesbury Park
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b1b8f46583d22e3c0ea9e8
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Digital Painting II: Forms in Still Life
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260409T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260409T200000
UID:69b9e3e267801235ed72c6dc@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:In this advanced workshop participants will be taken step by s
 tep through creating a still life digital painting from a photo reference
  in Adobe Photoshop. We will be using a Wacom drawing tablet. The instruct
 or will touch base on important art principles relating to form\, that wil
 l be applied to painting in Adobe Photoshop.\nPrior experience with drawin
 g tablets and Photoshop is required for this class. Though\, we will brief
 ly go over the user interface and various tools we will be using. If you a
 re looking for an introduction class or an in depth look at the broader a
 spects of Photoshop please look out for our\nDigital Painting I: Introduct
 ion & Pen Control\nor\nIntroduction to Photo Editing in Photoshop\nprogram
 s.\nFor more information about this program please contact dihonline@tpl.c
