BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Digital Filmmaking Basics
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260425T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260425T160000
UID:69976fa96724c63d00f3d260@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Recording a video is one thing\, but making movies is a whole 
 other ballgame. In this class we’ll look at how to use the manual settin
 gs on a digital camera to get that “cinematic” look as well as things 
 such as frame rates\, composition\, lighting\, and aspect ratios.\nCamera 
 equipment will be provided for this class. Participants are also welcome t
 o bring their own camera.\nRegistration is required.\nInformation Collecti
 on Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toro
 nto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)
 \, and 20(d). The information will only be used for event and program regi
 stration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handle
 s your information can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.
 ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Lillian H. Smith\, Bagshaw Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69976fa96724c63d00f3d260
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Coding with Python V
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260331T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260331T200000
UID:6974f1ca3cc3e0c9ecb474d2@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Python is an open source programming language that is used for
  creating web applications\, web content\, mathematics and system scriptin
 g. In this follow up course we will take a break from the logical side of 
 back-end development and get our feet wet with a little bit of front-end c
 oding\; we'll make a user interface! Using tkinter\, a popular module for 
 creating user-facing layouts\, we will design and implement a simple but e
 ffective UI for our Python code. This will allow us to run our programs us
 ing another platform other than Terminal.\nThis class is for beginners but
  assumes you have a basic understanding of Python or have attended Coding 
 with Python I\, II\, III\, and IV.\nRegistration will start 2 weeks before
  this class. Computers will be provided.\nInformation Collection Notice:\n
 The personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public L
 ibrary under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d)
 . The information will only be used for event and program registration\, d
 elivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your infor
 mation can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-3
 97-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Riverdale\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/6974f1ca3cc3e0c9ecb474d2
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
