BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:AI and the Environment with Han Qiao
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260504T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260504T210000
UID:69a72bdc8089f23c675f88e7@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Join our Innovator in Residence\, Joel S. Silver\, in conversa
 tion with Han Qiao about AI and the environment.\nHan Qiao is a PhD candid
 ate at the University of Toronto\, Faculty of Information\, and a member o
 f the Just Sustainability Design Lab. Han’s current research sits in the
  intersection of human-computer interaction\, design and urban planning. H
 er ongoing projects look into how people interact with data and data tools
  to imagine and navigate sustainable futures. Previously\, Han has conduct
 ed research in designing creativity support tools and investigating questi
 ons related to human-AI interaction.\nThis program is part of the Innovato
 r in Residence (AI and Music Production) program\, which is designed to he
 lp beginner and intermediate learners build knowledge and creative skills 
 and get hands-on with current AI tools in music production and learn about
