BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Diamond Painting
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260422T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260422T170000
UID:69af3c2381b67dfe32ab7918@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Diamond painting is a relaxing craft that combines paint-by-nu
 mbers and mosaics\, allowing you to create shimmering\, 3D masterpieces by
  applying tiny resin "diamonds" to a coded\, adhesive canvas. It is a medi
 tative\, low-mess activity that reduces stress\, making it accessible to b
 eginners and experienced crafters alike.\nRegistration is required. For a
 ges 7-12 only (children outside of this age range will not be able to part
 icipate).\n*For all registered Children's programs at Malvern\, there is a
  grace period of 10 minutes. After the first 10 minutes of a program\, spo
 ts will be given to waiting customers.*\nInformation Collection Notice:\nT
 he personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Public Li
 brary under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d).
  The information will only be used for event and program registration\, de
 livery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your inform
