BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Open Mic at Toronto Reference Library (Music\, Poetry & Storytelli
 ng)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260327T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260327T200000
UID:696ad89d94297d3600a5a861@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Are you a musician\, poet\, or storyteller? If so\, then you a
 re invited to share your talents at the Toronto Reference Library Open Mic
 ! Please note: stand-up comedy is no longer featured at this event.\nGuita
 r and piano provided. 5 minutes for each performance. Program is for adul
 ts\, teens\, and seniors.\nSign-up is at 5:30 pm. For more information\, p
 lease contact the Arts Department at 416-393-7157.\n**\nAccessibility at T
 oronto Public Library:\nToronto Public Library is committed to accessibili
 ty. Please call or email us if you are Deaf or have a disability and would
  like to request accommodation to participate in this program. Please let 
 us know as far in advance as possible and we will do our best to meet your
  request. At least three weeks notice is preferred. Phone 416-393-7099 or 
 email accessibleservices@tpl.ca.
LOCATION:Toronto Reference Library\, Browsery
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/696ad89d94297d3600a5a861
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
