BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Coding with Python II
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260414T200000
UID:69b60d868d5e2d0933655f75@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Python is an open source programming language that is used for
  creating web applications\, web content\, mathematics and system scriptin
 g. In this second Python session we will leverage everything we learned a
 bout loops and blocks in part one to create our very own functions. We'll 
 take a look at how to approach function design\, how to allow users to ent
 er data into functions through arguments\, and how to get our functions to
  return results. We will also introduce some new data structures which\, u
 nlike variables\, can hold more than one piece of data at a time.\nThis cl
 ass is for beginners but assumes you have a basic understanding of Python 
 or have attended Coding with Python I.\nRegistration will start 2 weeks be
 fore this class. Computers will be provided.\nInformation Collection Notic
 e:\nThe personal information on this form is collected by the Toronto Publ
 ic Library under the Public Libraries Act\, sections 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 2
 0(d). The information will only be used for event and program registration
 \, delivery and evaluation. Questions about how the library handles your i
 nformation can be directed to Answerline staff at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 4
 16-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4W 2G8.
LOCATION:Danforth/Coxwell\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b60d868d5e2d0933655f75
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
