BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Introduction to 3D Printing
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260409T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260409T190000
UID:69b9a8964dacf581ff829f64@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Learn how 3D printers work and how you can print at the Toront
 o Public Library’s Digital Innovation Hubs. In this lecture\, we will c
 over:\nBasics of 3D Printing\nHow to prepare a 3D design file for printing
  on a Prusa 3D printer using PrusaSlicer\nHow to access and use 3D printer
 s at the Digital Innovation Hubs at the Toronto Public Library\nBest prac
 tice for 3D printing and where to find designs\nReview of the rules and gu
 idelines for using 3D printers at the Toronto Public Library\nRegistratio
 n is required.\nNote: Customers are no longer required to attend a mandato
 ry 3D printing class prior to using a 3D printer at the Toronto Public Lib
 rary’s Digital Innovation Hubs. This class is for those who are interest
 ed in learning more about 3D printing and how to use the Prusa software.\n
 Information Collection Notice:\nThe personal information on this form is c
 ollected by the Toronto Public Library under the Public Libraries Act\, se
 ctions 20(a)\, 20(c)\, and 20(d). The information will only be used for ev
 ent and program registration\, delivery and evaluation. Questions about ho
 w the library handles your information can be directed to Answerline staff
  at\nanswerline@tpl.ca\n\, 416-397-5981\, 789 Yonge Street\, Toronto ON M4
 W 2G8.
LOCATION:Albert Campbell\, 2nd floor Digital Innovation Hub
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69b9a8964dacf581ff829f64
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
