BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:FRESH Movie Saturdays
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260328T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260328T130000
UID:69c1659f2866a5b48843df06@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:This program helps people stay active\, make friends\, learn n
 ew skills\, and have fun. Meet new folks\, build connections\, and tell us
  about programs and services you would like to see in the neighbourhood!\n
 Come join us every Saturday for screenings of your favourite movies. In ad
 dition to this\, enjoy cuddles with a therapy dog! Therapy dog Goose visi
 ts Fort York Branch on alternate Saturdays from 11:00AM-12:00PM.\nWe'll b
 e showing the following films:\nMarch 21-October Sky\nMarch 28-Agent Cod
 y Banks\nApril 4-Honey I Shrunk the Kids\nApril 11-Hachi:A Dog's Tale\nApr
 il 18-Zootopia\nApril 25-How to Train Your Dragon(2010)\nMay 2-Wonder\nMay
  9-Stuart Little\nMay 16-The Jungle Book(1967)\nMay 23-The Water Horse\nMa
 y 30-Two Brothers\nDrop-ins are welcome.\nThis program is in collaboration
  with\nGerstein Crisis Centre's F.R.E.S.H. initiative\n.
LOCATION:Fort York\, Urban Living Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c1659f2866a5b48843df06
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
