BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Branch Art Exhibit: Herstory: Spirit of Filipina Struggle\, Story 
 and Mythology by Jenniffer Twu
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260401T000000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T235959
UID:69c168bf567ba1dd31fe4320@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:Throughout April works by Jenniffer Twu are on display at Bloo
 r Gladstone Library.\nJenniffer Twu is a self-taught Canadian painter. She
  has exhibited her works at the Toronto Centre for the Arts. Her works are
  displayed at the North York General Hospital\, Sunnybrook Hospital and C
 AMH. Jenniffer states  "My collection of paintings are from an eye of so
 meone who witnessed Filipina struggles\, stories and mythologies. “Kasay
 sayan” is Herstory and “Diwa” is Spirit. I paint of the colourfulne
 ss of a culture\, the staunchness of a heritage and the intricateness of i
 ts story-telling. It is in my roots that I’ve grown into a Canadian art
 ist."\nImage credit: Jenniffer Twu\, Herstory: Spirit\nMedium: Acrylic
LOCATION:Bloor/Gladstone\, Program Room
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c168bf567ba1dd31fe4320
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Youth Hub: Yes\, You Can Win Scholarships
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260430T170000
UID:69c18ae2b48451fc3c0ac35e@tpl.bibliocommons.com
DESCRIPTION:​Scholarships are accessible to more students than what is c
 ommonly believed. And here is the most important thing: scholarships can b
 e a game changer for a student’s career\, their financial well-being\, a
 nd their or their family’s bank account. Scholarships\, grants\, and bur
 saries are available for high school\, college\, and university students\,
  and you don’t need perfect grades! This presentation\, led by Christop
 her Grafos\, will help empower attendees with information to find and win 
 money for postsecondary education.\nAll teens are welcome! Drop-in\, no re
 gistration required.\nThis program is part of Youth Hub service. Youth Hub
 s are a welcoming place for teens after school and in the summer\, where h
 elpful staff are always available. Free\, nutritious snacks are offered d
 aily. Drop by a branch with a\nYouth Hub\nor call the branch to find out 
 more.
LOCATION:Northern District\, Youth Hub (on the second floor)
URL:https://tpl.bibliocommons.com/v2/events/69c18ae2b48451fc3c0ac35e
X-SOURCE:Toronto Public Library
END:VEVENT
